ct form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"recaptcha\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"WPForms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3:\"amp\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=499255\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:589:\"<p>Do you want to create an AMP-friendly contact form? AMP or Accelerated Mobile Pages is a technology by Google that loads your web pages quickly on mobile devices. In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to create a contact form that&#8217;ll load on your AMP pages without any hassle. We&#8217;ll also explain how to add [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-an-amp-friendly-contact-form-for-wordpress/\">How to Create an AMP-Friendly Contact Form for WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Sandipan Mukherjee\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18734:\"<p>Do you want to create an AMP-friendly contact form? AMP or Accelerated Mobile Pages is a technology by Google that loads your web pages quickly on mobile devices.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to create a contact form that&#8217;ll load on your AMP pages without any hassle. We&#8217;ll also explain how to add reCAPTCHA to your AMP contact form to protect it from spammers.</p>\n<h3>Creating an AMP-Friendly Contact Form in WordPress</h3>\n<p>AMP (Accelerated Mobile Pages) provides the best experience to people with a slow internet connection. It loads the pages faster on mobile devices and thus, helps you to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">improve the traffic to your website</a>.</p>\n<p>However, AMP comes with a number of challenges for website owners.</p>\n<p>One of them is it allows limited usage of resources in order to load the pages faster. Thus, some functionalities won&#8217;t work on your AMP pages as they would normally.</p>\n<p>So what will happen to the contact form on your website? Will it work properly?</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re using the WPForms plugin, then it&#8217;ll automatically detect whether the form is loading on an AMP page or not. And then, it&#8217;ll display the link to the non-AMP version of the page to load the form properly.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-503827\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/contact-form-link-on-amp-page.png\" alt=\"Contact Form link on AMP page\" width=\"558\" height=\"203\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/contact-form-link-on-amp-page.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/contact-form-link-on-amp-page-300x109.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>However, you can also add a form to your AMP page instead of showing the above message.</p>\n<p>To do that, you&#8217;ll have to use the WPForms Lite plugin and then create a form that is fully compatible with AMP.</p>\n<p>So without further ado, let&#8217;s take a look at the step by step process to create an AMP-friendly contact form for your WordPress site.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install the AMP Plugin</h3>\n<p>The first thing you need to do is installand activate the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/amp/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">official Google AMP plugin for WordPress</a>.This free plugin is essential for adding AMP support to your website.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-503819\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/official-amp-plugin-for-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Official AMP plugin for WordPress\" width=\"558\" height=\"181\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/official-amp-plugin-for-wordpress.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/official-amp-plugin-for-wordpress-300x97.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>You may check out the step by step guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a> for detailed instructions.</p>\n<p>Once activated, this plugin automatically adds AMP support to your site. However, you can still make changes to the settings by visiting the <strong>Settings</strong>  <strong>AMP</strong> page.</p>\n<p>For more details, you can follow the guide on <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wp-tutorials/how-to-properly-setup-google-amp-on-your-wordpress-site/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">how to properly set up Google AMP</a>on your WordPress site.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Create a WordPress Form</h3>\n<p>It&#8217;s time to create a contact form with the help of the WPForms Lite plugin.</p>\n<p>To get things started, you&#8217;ll have to install and activate the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpforms-lite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">WPForms Lite plugin</a>. Upon activation, you need to go to <strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>Add New</strong> to create a new form.</p>\n<p>On the <strong>Setup</strong> page, you&#8217;ll find some default form templates. These templates allow you to speed up the process of creating the form. You can also use the blank form template to build a form from scratch.</p>\n<p>Since we want to create a contact form, go ahead and click on the <strong>Simple Contact Form</strong> template.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-501635\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/simple-contact-form-template.png\" alt=\"Simple Contact Form template\" width=\"1116\" height=\"522\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/simple-contact-form-template.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/simple-contact-form-template-300x140.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/simple-contact-form-template-768x359.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/simple-contact-form-template-1024x479.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>This will take you to the Form Builder page whereyou can easily add or remove a field. For example, if you want to add a subject field, then simply drag and drop the <strong>Single Line Text</strong> field from the left panel to your form.</p>\n<p>And to change the field name, you need to click on the field in the right panel and then, make changes to the label in the left panel.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-505440\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/customizing-a-field-of-the-amp-friendly-contact-form.png\" alt=\"Customizing field of the AMP-friendly contact form\" width=\"1116\" height=\"582\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/customizing-a-field-of-the-amp-friendly-contact-form.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/customizing-a-field-of-the-amp-friendly-contact-form-300x156.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/customizing-a-field-of-the-amp-friendly-contact-form-768x401.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/customizing-a-field-of-the-amp-friendly-contact-form-1024x534.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>The best part is you&#8217;ll be able to see the changes live. Cool, isn&#8217;t it?</p>\n<p>Similarly, you can edit the other form fields the way you want. You can also follow our step by step tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-simple-contact-form-in-wordpress/\">how to create a simple contact form in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done with the customization part, you can head over to the form <strong>Settings</strong> page from the left sidebar of the form builder. Here you&#8217;ll be able to change the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/setup-form-notification-wpforms/\">notification</a>and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-create-conditional-form-confirmations/\">confirmation settings</a>.</p>\n<p>Finally, you need to store the changes by clicking on the <strong>Save</strong> button, present at the top-right corner of your screen.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-502360\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/amp-friendly-contact-form-settings.png\" alt=\"AMP-friendly contact form settings\" width=\"1116\" height=\"520\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/amp-friendly-contact-form-settings.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/amp-friendly-contact-form-settings-300x140.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/amp-friendly-contact-form-settings-768x358.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/amp-friendly-contact-form-settings-1024x477.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s all! You don&#8217;t need to configure anything else. The WPForms Lite plugin will automatically add full AMP compatibility to your form now.</p>\n<p>In addition, you can add reCAPTCHA support to your AMP contact form to protect it from spammers.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s show you how to do it in the next step.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Register Your Website to Get reCAPTCHA Keys</h3>\n<p>ReCAPTCHA is a spam filtering service by Google. It helps you to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-build-spam-free-wordpress-contact-forms-the-ultimate-guide/\">protect your website from spammers</a> and automated bots.</p>\n<p>To use it on your site,you&#8217;ll have to register your site on the Google reCAPTCHA website so that you can get the site key and the secret key for your website.</p>\n<p>And then you can use them to add reCAPTCHA support to your AMP-friendly contact form.</p>\n<p>So head over to the <a href=\"https://www.google.com/recaptcha/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Google reCaptcha website</a> and then click on the <strong>Admin console</strong> button, present at the top-right corner of your screen.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-502422\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/google-recaptcha-website.png\" alt=\"Google reCAPTCHA website\" width=\"1116\" height=\"561\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/google-recaptcha-website.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/google-recaptcha-website-300x151.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/google-recaptcha-website-768x386.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/google-recaptcha-website-1024x515.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Google will now ask you to sign in to your account. After that, you&#8217;ll be redirected to the reCAPTCHA dashboard.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;ve previously configured a reCAPTCHA with this account, then you&#8217;ll have to click on the plus (+) icon to register your new site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-505340\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/register-button-to-add-your-site.png\" alt=\"Register button to add your site\" width=\"1116\" height=\"321\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/register-button-to-add-your-site.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/register-button-to-add-your-site-300x86.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/register-button-to-add-your-site-768x221.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/register-button-to-add-your-site-1024x295.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>However, if you&#8217;re using this account for the first time, then you&#8217;ll automatically see the &#8220;Register a new site&#8221; page after logging to your account.</p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;re on that page, you should write any name of your choice in the <strong>Label</strong> field for future reference.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-505346\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-recaptcha-v3-radio-button.png\" alt=\"Select reCAPTCHA v3 radio button\" width=\"1116\" height=\"591\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-recaptcha-v3-radio-button.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-recaptcha-v3-radio-button-300x159.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-recaptcha-v3-radio-button-768x407.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-recaptcha-v3-radio-button-1024x542.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you need to select the type of reCAPTCHA that you want to use.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s important to note that reCAPTCHA V2 is not supported by AMP. So you&#8217;ll have to select &#8220;reCAPTCHA V3&#8221; to add reCAPTCHA support to your AMP-friendly contact form.</p>\n<p>In the <strong>Domain</strong> field, you should write the domain name (without http:// or www) of your website where you want to add reCAPTCHA support. You can also add multiple domains or subdomains by clicking on the plus (+) icon.</p>\n<p>As far as the <strong>Owners</strong> field is concerned, your email address will be present there by default. However, you can add another email address if you want.</p>\n<p>Finally, select the &#8220;Accept the reCAPTCHA Terms of Service&#8221; checkbox and then, scroll down to the bottom of the page to click on the <strong>Submit</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-505347\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/accept-recaptcha-terms.png\" alt=\"Accept reCAPTCHA terms\" width=\"1116\" height=\"717\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/accept-recaptcha-terms.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/accept-recaptcha-terms-300x193.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/accept-recaptcha-terms-768x493.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/accept-recaptcha-terms-1024x658.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll now see a success message along with the site key and the secret key of your website.You need to copy these keys as you&#8217;ll have to use them on your WordPress site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-505409\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/copy-site-and-secret-key.png\" alt=\"Copy site and secret key\" width=\"1116\" height=\"543\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/copy-site-and-secret-key.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/copy-site-and-secret-key-300x146.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/copy-site-and-secret-key-768x374.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/copy-site-and-secret-key-1024x498.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>But before that, there&#8217;s one last thing that you should do.</p>\n<p>First, you need to click on the <strong>Go to Settings</strong> link. Next, scroll down to the bottom of the page and then select the &#8220;Allow this key to work with AMP pages&#8221; checkbox.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-505408\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-recaptcha-to-work-with-amp-pages.png\" alt=\"Allow reCAPTCHA to work with AMP pages\" width=\"1116\" height=\"468\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-recaptcha-to-work-with-amp-pages.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-recaptcha-to-work-with-amp-pages-300x126.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-recaptcha-to-work-with-amp-pages-768x322.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-recaptcha-to-work-with-amp-pages-1024x429.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>This is required for making the reCAPTCHA v3 work on the AMP pages. Once done, you need to click on the <strong>Save</strong> button to store the changes.</p>\n<h3>Step 4: Add reCAPTCHA to Your Contact Form</h3>\n<p>To get started, you&#8217;ll have to add the site key and the secret key to your website.</p>\n<p>So head over to your WordPress site andgo to the <strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>Settings</strong> page from the left sidebar of your WordPress admin panel.</p>\n<p>Next, you need to click on the <strong>reCAPTCHA</strong> tab to tweak the settings.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-505422\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-recaptcha-settings-page.png\" alt=\"WPForms reCAPTCHA settings page\" width=\"1116\" height=\"581\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-recaptcha-settings-page.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-recaptcha-settings-page-300x156.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-recaptcha-settings-page-768x400.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-recaptcha-settings-page-1024x533.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Here, you&#8217;ll have to select &#8220;reCAPTCHA v3&#8221; as the type, and then paste the site and secret keys to the respective fields.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-505427\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/add-site-and-secret-key.png\" alt=\"Add site and secret key\" width=\"1116\" height=\"332\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/add-site-and-secret-key.png 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/add-site-and-secret-key-300x89.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/add-site-and-secret-key-768x228.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/add-site-and-secret-key-1024x305.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Once done, you need to scroll down and click on the <strong>Save Settings</strong> button to store the changes.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s time to add reCAPTCHA to the AMP-friendly contact form.</p>\n<p>To do that, you need to head over to <strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>All Forms</strong> and then click on the title of your form to open it.</p>\n<p>Next, go to the <strong>Settings</strong>  <strong>General</strong> page and then check the &#8220;Enable Google v3 reCAPTCHA&#8221; option. And don&#8217;t forget to click on the <strong>Save</strong> button to store the changes.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-505434 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/enable-google-v3-recaptcha.png\" alt=\"Enable Google v3 reCAPTCHA amp-friendly contact form\" width=\"1118\" height=\"534\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/enable-google-v3-recaptcha.png 1118w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/enable-google-v3-recaptcha-300x143.png 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/enable-google-v3-recaptcha-768x367.png 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/enable-google-v3-recaptcha-1024x489.png 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1118px) 100vw, 1118px\" /></p>\n<p>Congratulations! You&#8217;ve successfully createdan AMP-friendly contact form for your WordPress site. You&#8217;ve also added reCAPTCHA to this form to protect it from spammers.</p>\n<p>If you liked this article, then you may also want to check out our step by step tutorial on<a href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-survey-form-in-wordpress-step-by-step/\">how to create a simple survey form in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, please follow us on <a href=\"http://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> to get updates from our blog.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-an-amp-friendly-contact-form-for-wordpress/\">How to Create an AMP-Friendly Contact Form for WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"https://wpforms.com/create-an-amp-friendly-contact-form-for-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:2;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:56:\"How to Display Survey Results Graphically (the Easy Way)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:43:\"https://wpforms.com/display-survey-results/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"https://wpforms.com/display-survey-results/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 03 Jul 2019 12:00:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"WordPress Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"survey\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"survey reporting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5:\"polls\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"survey form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=504277\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:560:\"<p>Are you ready to take the user data you&#8217;ve collected and build a survey results report with charts and graphs? In order to use your survey responses to grow your business, you need to be able to visualize all that data. In this tutorial, we&#8217;ll show you exactly how to display survey results graphically using [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/display-survey-results/\">How to Display Survey Results Graphically (the Easy Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11927:\"<p>Are you ready to take the user data you&#8217;ve collected and build a survey results report with charts and graphs? In order to use your survey responses to grow your business, you need to be able to visualize all that data. In this tutorial, we&#8217;ll show you exactly how to display survey results graphically using WPForms.</p>\n<h3>How Do You Read Survey Results?</h3>\n<p>Here&#8217;s a simple and quick process for how to analyze survey data:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Create a visual representation</li>\n<li>Look for patterns</li>\n<li>Decide what action the results call for</li>\n</ol>\n<p>We all know the human brain loves visuals. So following the above steps can help you spot potential issues with things like customer satisfaction so you can fix them and <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/make-money-online/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">make more money online</a>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><div class=\"alert alert-warning\"><p>Need more data? Check out this great post on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-increase-survey-response-rates-and-build-your-business/\">how to increase survey response rates</a>for some quick tips!</p>\n</div></p>\n<p>So now that you know how to read survey results, let&#8217;s learn how to make a pie chart from a survey for quick data visualization.</p>\n<h3>How to Make a Pie Chart from a Survey</h3>\n<p>So, how do you read survey results quickly? Well, one of the easiest ways is to make a pie chart from a survey.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at how it&#8217;s done in WPForms using the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/surveys-and-polls-addon/\">Survey and Polls addon</a>.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Find Your Survey Results</h3>\n<p>First, head over to the WPForms settings in the left hand panel of your WordPress dashboard and click on <strong>All Forms</strong>to locate your survey form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-504294\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-display-survey-results-in-excel-2.jpg\" alt=\"how to display survey results in excel\" width=\"1116\" height=\"614\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-display-survey-results-in-excel-2.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-display-survey-results-in-excel-2-300x165.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-display-survey-results-in-excel-2-768x423.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-display-survey-results-in-excel-2-1024x563.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, hover your mouse over your survey form and click on <strong>Survey Results</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-504297\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/data-visualization-survey-results-example.jpg\" alt=\"data visualization survey results example\" width=\"1116\" height=\"615\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/data-visualization-survey-results-example.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/data-visualization-survey-results-example-300x165.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/data-visualization-survey-results-example-768x423.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/data-visualization-survey-results-example-1024x564.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /><a id=\"remove-post-thumbnail\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-admin/post.php?post=504277&amp;action=edit#\">Remove featured image</a></p>\n<h3>Step 2: Generate Your Pie Chart</h3>\n<p>Now, click on the pie chart icon on the upper right side of your survey results dashboard and your pie chart will be automatically generated.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-504312\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-graphically-display-survey-data.gif\" alt=\"how to graphically display survey data\" width=\"1116\" height=\"610\" /></p>\n<p>This works with <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-net-promoter-score-nps-survey-in-wordpress/\">Net Promoter Score (NPS) surveys</a> as well.</p>\n<p>And check this out </p>\n<p>Want to regenerate the colors on your pie chart graph?</p>\n<p>Simply click on any other chart icon then back to the pie chart icon to change the color of all the sections.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-504306\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/human-brain-pie-chart-graph.gif\" alt=\"human brain pie chart graph\" width=\"1116\" height=\"444\" /></p>\n<p>And there it is. These 2 simple steps get you a beautiful pie chart in just seconds.</p>\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve got the basics down and created your pie chart, let&#8217;s learn more details about how to display survey results graphically (the easy way, of course).</p>\n<h3>How to Display Survey Results Graphically</h3>\n<p>So you&#8217;re asking yourself how to graph survey results? Whether you&#8217;re using a survey results infographic template or a presentation software like PowerPoint, it&#8217;s easy to display survey results graphically with WPForms.</p>\n<p>Here&#8217;s how:</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Generate Your Charts and Graphs</h3>\n<p>The steps above showed you how to make a pie chart and generate your graphs. You can also follow those steps to create line charts and vertical or horizontal bar graphs by clicking on the icons for the different chart types. With WPForms, your data is automatically generated into beautiful reports that are easy for the human brain to understand.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-504320\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-chart-for-survey-results.jpg\" alt=\"How do I make a chart for survey results\" width=\"1116\" height=\"431\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-chart-for-survey-results.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-chart-for-survey-results-300x116.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-chart-for-survey-results-768x297.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-chart-for-survey-results-1024x395.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>And you can also scroll down the page in this section to find Likert Scale survey responses.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-504831\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-export-data-in-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"1116\" height=\"420\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-export-data-in-wordpress.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-export-data-in-wordpress-300x113.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-export-data-in-wordpress-768x289.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/how-to-export-data-in-wordpress-1024x385.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>For this tutorial, let&#8217;s stay at the top of the page and move forward with exporting the pie chart.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Export Your Charts and Graphs</h3>\n<p>Now, click on the dropdown in the top right corner that says Export.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-504324\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-responses-and-chart-types.jpg\" alt=\"survey responses and chart types\" width=\"1116\" height=\"431\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-responses-and-chart-types.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-responses-and-chart-types-300x116.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-responses-and-chart-types-768x297.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-responses-and-chart-types-1024x395.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Here, you can choose between saving as a JPG or a PDF, or to print the graph.</p>\n<p>For this example, let&#8217;s save the graph as a standard image file (JPG) so we can easily embed it into a survey report.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-504328\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-pie-chart-for-survey-results.jpg\" alt=\"How do I make a pie chart for survey results\" width=\"1116\" height=\"445\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-pie-chart-for-survey-results.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-pie-chart-for-survey-results-300x120.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-pie-chart-for-survey-results-768x306.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/How-do-I-make-a-pie-chart-for-survey-results-1024x408.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Repeat this step with each graph you&#8217;d like to use in your report.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Embed Your Charts and Graphs</h3>\n<p>Now that you have generated JPGs of all of the charts you need to display your survey results, you can easily embed them into presentation software or asurvey results infographic template.</p>\n<p>This is especially helpful if you&#8217;re on a team and you&#8217;d like to present the survey results to other people.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.google.com/slides/about/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Google Slides</a> is a great (and free!) place to start embedding your graphs and displaying your survey data graphically.</p>\n<h3>Presenting Open-Ended Survey Results</h3>\n<p>One of the quickest and easiest ways to present surveys with open-ended questions is to create word clouds. And you can do it in seconds with<a href=\"https://www.jasondavies.com/wordcloud/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">this fantastic free Word Clouds generator.</a></p>\n<p>For instance, when we input the text of this article into the generator, we created this survey results example image:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-504341 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-results-infographic-template-word-clouds.jpg\" alt=\"infographic template word clouds\" width=\"1116\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-results-infographic-template-word-clouds.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-results-infographic-template-word-clouds-300x161.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-results-infographic-template-word-clouds-768x413.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/survey-results-infographic-template-word-clouds-1024x551.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Pretty cool, right? And you can save your word clouds and embed them into your graphical survey reports for an impressive survey <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/survey-data-visualization-tools/\">data visualization</a> trick that really helps summarize all those open-ended responses.</p>\n<h3>In Conclusion</h3>\n<p>That&#8217;s it! You now know how to display survey results graphically. We hope this post helped show you how easy charting your site&#8217;s survey data can be!</p>\n<p>Need to setup your first survey? Check out our step by step guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-survey-form-in-wordpress-step-by-step/\">how to create a simple survey form in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<p>What are you waiting for? Get started with the most powerful<a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WordPress forms plugin</a>today.</p>\n<p>If you like this article, then please follow us on<a href=\"http://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Facebook</a>and<a href=\"https://twitter.com/easywpforms?lang=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Twitter</a>for more free WordPress tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/display-survey-results/\">How to Display Survey Results Graphically (the Easy Way)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:48:\"https://wpforms.com/display-survey-results/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"How to Create Jira Issues from WordPress Form Submissions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:71:\"https://wpforms.com/create-jira-issues-from-wordpress-form-submissions/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:79:\"https://wpforms.com/create-jira-issues-from-wordpress-form-submissions/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 27 Jun 2019 12:00:41 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"WordPress Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"wordpress form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"zapier\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"WPForms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"zapier addon\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=492073\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:591:\"<p>Do you want to create Jira issues automatically using your WordPress forms? Jira is an online tool that allows you to track the issues and bugs related to your software projects. In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to create Jira issues from WordPress form submissions without any hassle. Why Use a WordPress Form to [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-jira-issues-from-wordpress-form-submissions/\">How to Create Jira Issues from WordPress Form Submissions</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Sandipan Mukherjee\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:27015:\"<p>Do you want to create Jira issues automatically using your WordPress forms? Jira is an online tool that allows you to track the issues and bugs related to your software projects.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you how to create Jira issues from WordPress form submissions without any hassle.</p>\n<h3>Why Use a WordPress Form to Create Jira Issues?</h3>\n<p>Jira is a useful project management tool for developers. They can use this tool to keep track and prioritize their software related bugs and issues.</p>\n<p>Now, most of the bugs are usually found and reported by the users of the software. So you&#8217;ll have to manually create new issues in your Jira account once they are reported.</p>\n<p>However, this can be a time-consuming task for you.</p>\n<p>The best solution is to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">start a WordPress site</a> and then, use the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WPForms plugin</a> tocreate a bug submission form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490555\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-plugin-for-wordpress.png\" alt=\"WPForms plugin for WordPress\" width=\"558\" height=\"254\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-plugin-for-wordpress.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-plugin-for-wordpress-300x137.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>In case you don&#8217;t know, WPForms is a user-friendly form builder plugin. You can easily use its drag and drop interface to create any kind of form and then, embed it to your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll have to connect that form to your Jira account with the help of Zapier. This will help you to create new issues automatically in your <a href=\"https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Jira account</a>whenever someone submits the form.</p>\n<p>So without further ado, let&#8217;s take a look at the step by step process of creating Jira issues from WordPress form submissions.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Create a WordPress Form</h3>\n<p>To get things started, you&#8217;ll have to create a bug submission form with the help of the WPForms plugin.</p>\n<p>So install and activate the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/pricing/\">WPForms plugin</a>if you haven&#8217;t already done that. You can follow the step by step guide on <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a> for detailed instructions.</p>\n<p>The next thing you need to do is <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-form-templates-pack-addon/\">install the Form Templates Pack addon</a>. This addon offers 100+ additional form templates including the bug tracker form.</p>\n<p>So head over to <strong>WPForms</strong> <strong>Addons</strong>from the left sidebar of your admin panel.</p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll have to search for the <strong>Form Templates Pack</strong> addon on that page. Once you find it, you should install and activate the addon.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497288\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/form-templates-pack-addon.png\" alt=\"Form Templates Pack addon\" width=\"558\" height=\"233\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/form-templates-pack-addon.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/form-templates-pack-addon-300x125.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you need to go to <strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>Add New</strong> from the left sidebar of your WordPress admin panel. This will take you to the setup page where you can choose a template for your form.</p>\n<p>On this page, you need to search for the &#8220;Bug Tracker&#8221; form under the <strong>Additional Templates</strong> section.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497292\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bug-tracker-form-template.png\" alt=\"Bug Tracker form template\" width=\"558\" height=\"322\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bug-tracker-form-template.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bug-tracker-form-template-300x173.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you find it, you need to click on it to edit this template.</p>\n<p>You can easily add or remove fields from this form. For example, you should add a text field to this form and name it as <strong>Subject</strong>. This field will be used by your users to writebriefly about the bug or issue.</p>\n<p>You can also go to the settingspage to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/setup-form-notification-wpforms/\">configure the notification</a> and the<a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/setup-form-confirmation-wpforms/\">confirmation settings</a> of this form.</p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done, you need to save the changes by clicking on the <strong>Save</strong> button, present at the top-right corner of your screen.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497295\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/save-bug-tracker-form.png\" alt=\"Save Bug Tracker form\" width=\"558\" height=\"425\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/save-bug-tracker-form.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/save-bug-tracker-form-300x228.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<h3>Step 2: Add a Test Entry to Your Form</h3>\n<p>The next thing you need to do is add at least one test entry to your form. This will be required later for testing the connection between WPForms and Jira.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s use the preview option of the form to add a test entry.</p>\n<p>First, you need to head over to the<strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>All Forms</strong> page to view all your forms. And then, you&#8217;ll have to hover your mouse cursor over the title of the bug tracker form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-497296 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/preview-bug-tracker-form.png\" alt=\"Preview Bug Tracker form create jira issues\" width=\"558\" height=\"372\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/preview-bug-tracker-form.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/preview-bug-tracker-form-300x200.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll now see some options below the title of your form. Go ahead and click on the <strong>Preview</strong> link toopen your form in a new tab of your web browser.</p>\n<p>Finally, you need to fill in the form and then click on the <strong>Submit</strong> button to create a test form entry.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Install Zapier Addon</h3>\n<p>It&#8217;s time to install the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/zapier-addon/\">Zapier Addon</a> on your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>Wait! What is Zapier?<a href=\"https://zapier.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Zapier</a> is an automation tool that allows you to do a continuous task by connecting 2 or more apps.</p>\n<p>And we&#8217;ll be using Zapier to connect WPForms and Jira so that your site visitors can create issues in your Jira account automatically.</p>\n<p>To get started, you need to go to the<strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>Addons</strong> page and then search for the Zapier addon. Once you find it, you need to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/install-activate-wpforms-addons/\">install and activate the addon</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490404\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-and-activate-zapier-addon.png\" alt=\"Install and Activate Zapier addon\" width=\"558\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-and-activate-zapier-addon.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-and-activate-zapier-addon-300x121.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>The next thing you need to do is get the Zapier API key of your website. This will be required to connect your WPForms account to Zapier.</p>\n<p>So head over to the<strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>Settings</strong> page and then click on the <strong>Integrations</strong> tab.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490403\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/get-zapier-api-key-to-connect-wpforms-account.png\" alt=\"Get Zapier API key to connect WPForms account\" width=\"558\" height=\"373\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/get-zapier-api-key-to-connect-wpforms-account.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/get-zapier-api-key-to-connect-wpforms-account-300x201.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Here you&#8217;ll have to click on the Zapier icon to view the API key of your site. You should keep this page open as we&#8217;ll be using this API key in <strong>Step 5</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Step 4: Create a New Zap</h3>\n<p>A Zap is a process of connecting 2 or more apps in Zapier. And in this step, you&#8217;ll have to create a new Zap to connect WPForms to Jira software.</p>\n<p>First, you need to open the <a href=\"https://zapier.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Zapier</a> website in a new tab of your web browser. Here you can create a new account or log in to your existing account.</p>\n<p>On the Zapier dashboard page, you need to click on the <strong>Make a Zap!</strong> button, present at the top-right corner of your screen. This will open a new page to start the configuration wizard.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490412\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/make-a-zap-button.png\" alt=\"Make a Zap button\" width=\"558\" height=\"228\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/make-a-zap-button.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/make-a-zap-button-300x123.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Before starting the process, let&#8217;s understand what we&#8217;re doing here.</p>\n<p>A Zap requires 2 things to work properly: a trigger and an action. We&#8217;ll be configuring WPForms as the trigger app and Jira software as the action app.</p>\n<p>This will make sure that a new issue will be created in your Jira account whenever someone submits the form on your website.</p>\n<p>So without further ado, let&#8217;s proceed to the next step to set up the trigger app.</p>\n<h3>Step 5: Configure a Trigger App</h3>\n<p>First, you need to search for the WPForms app using the &#8220;Choose a Trigger App&#8221; search box. And then, you need to click on it once you find the app.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490420\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/choose-wpforms-as-a-trigger-app.png\" alt=\"Choose WPForms as a trigger app\" width=\"558\" height=\"167\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/choose-wpforms-as-a-trigger-app.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/choose-wpforms-as-a-trigger-app-300x90.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Zapier will now ask you to select a trigger option.</p>\n<p>Since WPForms offers just one trigger option, select <strong>New Form Entry</strong> and then click on the <strong>Save + Continue</strong> button to proceed.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490421\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-new-form-entry-as-wpforms-trigger-option.png\" alt=\"Select New Form Entry as WPForms trigger option\" width=\"558\" height=\"228\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-new-form-entry-as-wpforms-trigger-option.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-new-form-entry-as-wpforms-trigger-option-300x123.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll have to connect your WPForms account to Zapier.</p>\n<p>To do that, you need to click on the <strong>Connect an Account</strong> button. This will open a popup window where you need to enter your website URL and the Zapier API key.You may go back to <strong>Step 3</strong> to learn how to get the API key.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490419\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-wpforms-account.png\" alt=\"Allow Zapier to access WPForms account\" width=\"558\" height=\"393\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-wpforms-account.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-wpforms-account-300x211.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once done, you need to click on the <strong>Yes, Continue</strong> button to connect WPForms to Zapier.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll now see your WPForms account added to the &#8220;Select WPForms Account&#8221; page. You can also click on the <strong>Test</strong> button to check the connection between the 2 apps.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490434\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-connection-between-zapier-and-wpforms.png\" alt=\"Test Connection between Zapier and WPForms\" width=\"558\" height=\"274\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-connection-between-zapier-and-wpforms.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-connection-between-zapier-and-wpforms-300x147.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you get the success message, you can click on the <strong>Save + Continue</strong> button to proceed.</p>\n<p>Zapier will now retrieve all the forms of your website and then, will ask you to select a form from the dropdown box. So select the bug tracker form and then click on the <strong>Continue</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497303\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-bug-tracker-form-from-dropdown-menu.png\" alt=\"Select Bug Tracker form from dropdown menu\" width=\"558\" height=\"248\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-bug-tracker-form-from-dropdown-menu.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-bug-tracker-form-from-dropdown-menu-300x133.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>This will allow Zapier to fetch all the entries of your form.</p>\n<p>So go ahead and select any one of the form entries so that you can use it to test the connection between WPForms and Jira software.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490437\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-entry-for-testing-purpose.png\" alt=\"Select Form Entry for testing purpose\" width=\"558\" height=\"328\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-entry-for-testing-purpose.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-entry-for-testing-purpose-300x176.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once done, you need to click on the <strong>Continue</strong> button to complete the trigger setup process.</p>\n<h3>Step 6: Configure an Action App</h3>\n<p>Let&#8217;s configure Jira software as the action app now.</p>\n<p>To get started, you should click on the &#8220;Your Zap currently lacks an Action step. Add one now!&#8221; link. This will take you to the &#8220;Choose an Action App&#8221; page.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-490466 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/zap-lacks-an-action-app.png\" alt=\"Zap lacks an action app create jira issues\" width=\"558\" height=\"136\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/zap-lacks-an-action-app.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/zap-lacks-an-action-app-300x73.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Here you need to search for the Jira Software using the search box and then, click on it once you find the app.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-496862\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/configure-jira-software-as-an-action-app.png\" alt=\"Configure Jira Software as an action app\" width=\"558\" height=\"185\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/configure-jira-software-as-an-action-app.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/configure-jira-software-as-an-action-app-300x99.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll have to select a Jira action that&#8217;ll happen when someone submits your form.Since we want to create a new Jira issue, go ahead and search for <strong>Create Issue</strong> using the search box.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-496861\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-jira-software-action.png\" alt=\"Select Jira Software action\" width=\"558\" height=\"295\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-jira-software-action.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-jira-software-action-300x159.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you find it, you need to select &#8220;Create Issue&#8221; and then click on the <strong>Save + Continue</strong> button to proceed.</p>\n<p>Now you&#8217;ll have to connect your Jira account to Zapier. To do that, you need to click on the <strong>Connect an Account</strong> button.</p>\n<p>This will open a popup window which will ask you to select the version of the Jira software that you use. So select &#8220;I use Jira Software Cloud&#8221; from the dropdown menu and then click on the <strong>Yes, Continue</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497058\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-jira-account.png\" alt=\"Allow Zapier to access Jira account to create jira issues\" width=\"558\" height=\"274\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-jira-account.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-jira-account-300x147.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll be asked to provide permission to Zapier so that it can access and create issues in your Jira account. So go ahead and click on the <strong>Accept</strong> button to connect your Jira account to Zapier.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497059\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/authorize-zapier-by-clicking-on-accept-button.png\" alt=\"Authorize Zapier to create Jira issues by clicking on the Accept button\" width=\"558\" height=\"316\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/authorize-zapier-by-clicking-on-accept-button.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/authorize-zapier-by-clicking-on-accept-button-300x170.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll now see your Jira account added to the &#8220;Select Jira Software Account&#8221; page. You can click on the <strong>Test</strong> button to check the connection between WPForms and Jira software.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497077\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-jira-software-account.png\" alt=\"Test Jira Software account\" width=\"558\" height=\"277\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-jira-software-account.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-jira-software-account-300x149.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>After getting the success message, you can click on the <strong>Save + Continue</strong> button to go to the next step.</p>\n<h3>Step 7: Setup and Test the Jira Issues Template</h3>\n<p>In this step, you&#8217;ll have to configure the Jira Issues template. This template will be used by Zapier to create new issues in your Jira account.</p>\n<p>First, you need to select the project where you want to create new issues. This will be fetched from your Jira account.</p>\n<p>So go ahead and select the project name from the <strong>Project</strong> dropdown menu.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497317\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/set-up-template-to-create-jira-issues.png\" alt=\"Set up template to create Jira issues\" width=\"558\" height=\"216\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/set-up-template-to-create-jira-issues.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/set-up-template-to-create-jira-issues-300x116.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you need to select the <strong>Issue Type</strong> from the dropdown menu. It can be a task or a sub-task.</p>\n<p>Once done, you&#8217;ll see a number of new fields added to this template. The data for most of these fields will be fetched from your bug tracker form.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s configure some of the required fields in this template.</p>\n<p>For the <strong>Summary</strong> field, you need to click on the Insert a Field icon and then select &#8220;Subject&#8221; from the dropdown menu.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497316\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-jira-issues-template.png\" alt=\"Create Jira issues template\" width=\"558\" height=\"353\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-jira-issues-template.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-jira-issues-template-300x190.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>What about the <strong>Reporter</strong> field? There&#8217;s no option to send the name of the person who reported the bug in the reporter field. So you&#8217;ll have to select an existing user from your Jira account here.</p>\n<p>For the <strong>Description</strong> field,you should select &#8220;Describe what happened&#8221; from the dropdown menu. You can also add the name and email fields in the Description box to know who reported the bug to you.</p>\n<p>Once done, you should scroll down to the bottom of the page to click on the <strong>Continue</strong> button.</p>\n<p>Next, you need to click on the <strong>Send Test to Jira Software</strong> to test the connection between WPForms and Jira. This will create a new issue in your Jira account with your test entry.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497083\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/send-test-to-jira-software.png\" alt=\"Send test to create jira issue\" width=\"558\" height=\"162\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/send-test-to-jira-software.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/send-test-to-jira-software-300x87.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>You may also go to your Jira account to confirm the same.</p>\n<p>Next, you should return to the Zapier configuration wizard and click on the <strong>Finish</strong> button to complete the action app setup process.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497084\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-to-jira-zap.png\" alt=\"WPForms to Jira zap\" width=\"558\" height=\"329\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-to-jira-zap.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-to-jira-zap-300x177.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Lastly, you need to turn the toggle button to <strong>ON</strong>. You can also give a name of your choice to this Zap for future reference.</p>\n<h3>Step 8: Embed the Form to Your Website</h3>\n<p>The final step is to embed the form to your website so that your site visitors can use it to create new issues in your Jira account.</p>\n<p>You can easily embed a WPForms form to a post, page, or <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-add-a-contact-form-in-wordpress-sidebar-widget/\">the sidebar of your website</a>.</p>\n<p>However, let&#8217;s take a look at how to add it to a WordPress page. To do that, you need to head over to <strong>Pages</strong>  <strong>Add New</strong> from the left sidebar of your WordPress admin panel.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-490551 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/adding-wpforms-block-to-a-wordpress-page.png\" alt=\"Adding WPForms block to a WordPress page create jira issues\" width=\"558\" height=\"319\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/adding-wpforms-block-to-a-wordpress-page.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/adding-wpforms-block-to-a-wordpress-page-300x172.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Now you need to click on the Add block (<strong>+</strong>) icon to open the block manager and then search for the WPForms block.</p>\n<p>Once you find it, you should click on it to add the WPForms block to the editor.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490552\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-from-wpforms-dropdown-box.png\" alt=\"Select custom Airtable form from WPForms dropdown box\" width=\"558\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-from-wpforms-dropdown-box.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-from-wpforms-dropdown-box-300x128.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you need to select the bug tracker form from the &#8220;Select a Form&#8221; dropdown menu. This will insert the form to the page editor.</p>\n<p>After making the necessary changes, you can publish this page by clicking on the <strong>Publish</strong> button, present at the top-right corner of your screen.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-497318\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-jira-issues-wordpress-page.png\" alt=\"Create Jira issues WordPress page\" width=\"558\" height=\"366\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-jira-issues-wordpress-page.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-jira-issues-wordpress-page-300x197.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s all! You&#8217;ve successfully created a custom Jira issues form and embedded it to your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>We hope this tutorial helped you understand how to create Jira issues from WordPress form submissions.</p>\n<p>If you liked this article, then you should also check out our step by step tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-send-an-automatic-slack-invite-from-a-wordpress-form/\">how to send an automatic Slack invite from a WordPress form</a>.</p>\n<p>Also,please follow us on<a href=\"https://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Facebook</a>and<a href=\"https://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Twitter</a>to get updates from our blog.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-jira-issues-from-wordpress-form-submissions/\">How to Create Jira Issues from WordPress Form Submissions</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"https://wpforms.com/create-jira-issues-from-wordpress-form-submissions/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:65:\"How to Get an Unlimited Free Trial of WPForms (100% Free Forever)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"https://wpforms.com/unlimited-free-trial-wpforms/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://wpforms.com/unlimited-free-trial-wpforms/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 24 Jun 2019 12:00:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:6:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8