url.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9801:\"<p>Want to get WPForms completely for free? You can use WPForms Lite without spending a penny. In this post, we&#8217;ll show you how to get an unlimited free WPForms trial by using WPForms Lite.</p>\n<h3>What Is WPForms Lite?</h3>\n<p>WPForms Lite is the free version of WPForms, the world&#8217;s most popular WordPress form plugin. It lets you easily create, save, and publish forms on your WordPress websitewithout writing a single line of code.</p>\n<p>So how much is WPForms? You&#8217;ll be happy to learn that the WPForms Lite plugin is free, forever.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpforms-lite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-492292\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-most-user-friendly-wordpress-contact-form-plugin-in-the-market.jpg\" alt=\"wpforms most user friendly wordpress contact form plugin in the market\" width=\"558\" height=\"336\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-most-user-friendly-wordpress-contact-form-plugin-in-the-market.jpg 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-most-user-friendly-wordpress-contact-form-plugin-in-the-market-300x181.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></a></p>\n<p>And with this free trial of WPForms Lite (that never expires), you&#8217;ll get access to features that let you do things like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Create online forms for your site without writing any code</li>\n<li>Add and remove form fields easily with a drag and drop builder</li>\n<li>Collect leads with email subscription forms for your<a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/beginners-guide-to-email-marketing/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">email marketing</a></li>\n<li>Display beautiful <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/features/responsive-mobile-friendly/\">mobile-responsive</a> forms on your site</li>\n<li>Prevent spam submissions with <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/features/spam-protection/\">reCAPTCHA and Honeypot</a></li>\n<li>Get access to WPForms support</li>\n</ul>\n<p>On top of that, if you ever decide to <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/upgrade-wpforms-lite-paid-license/\">upgrade your WPForms account from Lite to Pro</a> (which is incredibly easy), you&#8217;ll instantly get access to additional WPForms addons and premium features that let you do things like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Accept payments online via PayPal and Stripe through web order forms</li>\n<li>Make beautiful <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/conversational-forms-addon/\">Conversational Forms</a></li>\n<li>Gather visitor insights with<a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/surveys-and-polls-addon/\">surveys and polls</a></li>\n<li>Use smart conditional logic to show or hide fields:</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/features/conditional-logic/\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-462788 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/nps-survey-enhanced-form-wpforms.gif\" alt=\"\" width=\"562\" height=\"628\" /></a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Collect user locations with the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/geolocation-addon/\">Geolocation addon</a></li>\n<li>Capture partial form entries with the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/addons/form-abandonment-addon/\">Form Abandonment addon</a></li>\n<li>Get priority customer support</li>\n<li>And <a href=\"http://wpforms.com/pricing\">a ton more</a>&#8230;</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How Do I Get a WPForms Trial for Free?</h3>\n<p>It&#8217;s easy to get WPForms free. To activate your unlimited free WPForms trial, all you need to do is download and install WPForms Lite.</p>\n<div class=\"alert alert-warning\"><p>Make sure you learn why you must avoid any <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-pro-nulled/\">WPForms Pro free downloads, WPForms nulled, or a WPForms Pro crack</a>you see floating around the web.</p>\n</div>\n<p>Next, we&#8217;ll walk you throughhow to install WPForms Lite on your WordPress site.</p>\n<h3>How Do I Install WPForms Free Version?</h3>\n<p>So if you&#8217;re ready to get your WPForms trial and download WPForms Lite (it&#8217;s free forever and ever!), make sure you&#8217;re using WordPress.org, not WordPress.com. For more details, check out our post on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/wordpress-com-vs-wordpress-org-pros-and-cons-compared/\">WordPress.org vs WordPress.com</a>.</p>\n<h3>Step 1:Install the Plugin</h3>\n<p>From your WordPress dashboard, head over to the panel on the left and hover over <strong>Plugins</strong> then select<strong>Add New</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-496429\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-smart-wordpress-sites.jpg\" alt=\"create smart wordpress sites\" width=\"1116\" height=\"679\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-smart-wordpress-sites.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-smart-wordpress-sites-300x183.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-smart-wordpress-sites-768x467.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-smart-wordpress-sites-1024x623.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, type the keyword &#8220;WPForms&#8221; into the search box on the top right corner.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-496449\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-contact-forms-find-wpforms-in-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"create contact forms find wpforms in wordpress\" width=\"1116\" height=\"619\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-contact-forms-find-wpforms-in-wordpress.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-contact-forms-find-wpforms-in-wordpress-300x166.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-contact-forms-find-wpforms-in-wordpress-768x426.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-contact-forms-find-wpforms-in-wordpress-1024x568.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, click on the grey<strong> Install Now</strong> button next to the plugin called Contact From by WPForms.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-496451\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-wpforms-lite-wordpress-forms-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"install wpforms lite wordpress forms plugin\" width=\"1116\" height=\"619\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-wpforms-lite-wordpress-forms-plugin.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-wpforms-lite-wordpress-forms-plugin-300x166.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-wpforms-lite-wordpress-forms-plugin-768x426.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-wpforms-lite-wordpress-forms-plugin-1024x568.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<h3>Step 2:Activate the Plugin</h3>\n<p>Next, click on the blue<strong>Activate</strong>button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-496613\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/plugin-for-form-entries-with-file-uploads.jpg\" alt=\"plugin for form entries with file uploads\" width=\"1116\" height=\"618\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/plugin-for-form-entries-with-file-uploads.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/plugin-for-form-entries-with-file-uploads-300x166.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/plugin-for-form-entries-with-file-uploads-768x425.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/plugin-for-form-entries-with-file-uploads-1024x567.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>And that&#8217;s it!</p>\n<p>Your WPForms free version is now ready to go and you can start making your first form right away. Next, click the video below to watch a walk-through or read our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/creating-first-form/\">how to create your first form</a>.</p>\n<p><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/yDyvSGV7tP4?rel=0\" width=\"560\" height=\"315\" frameborder=\"0\" allowfullscreen=\"allowfullscreen\"></iframe></p>\n<p>Brand new to WPForms and looking to get started with the<a href=\"http://wpforms.com/pricing\">WPForms Pro</a>version right away? Check out this post on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/install-wpforms-plugin/\">how to install and activate the WPForms plugin</a>for help setting up WPForms Pro.</p>\n<p>Wondering what else you can do with WPForms? Check out these articles:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-export-wordpress-form-entries-to-csv/\">How to Export WordPress Form Entries to CSV</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-build-spam-free-wordpress-contact-forms-the-ultimate-guide/\">How to Build Spam-Free WordPress Contact Forms</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://wpforms.com/wpforms-power-hacks-to-grow-your-business-online/\">WPForms Power Hacks To Grow Your Business Online</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3>In Conclusion</h3>\n<p>So now that you know exactly how to get an WPForms trial and use WPForms for free, tell your friends! And for more free things to use on your website, check out our handy guide of the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-free-wordpress-plugins-for-your-website/\">best free WordPress plugins.</a></p>\n<p>So what are you waiting for? Get started with the <a href=\"http://wpforms.com\">most powerful WordPress forms plugin</a> today.</p>\n<p>And if you like this article, then please follow us on <a href=\"https://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> and <a href=\"http://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Twitter</a> for more from the blog.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/unlimited-free-trial-wpforms/\">How to Get an Unlimited Free Trial of WPForms (100% Free Forever)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"https://wpforms.com/unlimited-free-trial-wpforms/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"How to Choose the Best WordPress Hosting (Ultimate Guide for 2019)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:49:\"https://wpforms.com/best-wordpress-hosting-guide/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:57:\"https://wpforms.com/best-wordpress-hosting-guide/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 20 Jun 2019 12:00:47 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"web hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:17:\"wordpress hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:15:\"managed hosting\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=494565\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:586:\"<p>Launching a new website and looking for the best WordPress hosting company for your needs? There are 100&#8217;s of WordPress hosting companies out there, and choosing the right one for your site can improve your SEO and boost your sales. In this guide, we&#8217;ll discuss how to choose the best WordPress hosting service and the [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-wordpress-hosting-guide/\">How to Choose the Best WordPress Hosting (Ultimate Guide for 2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25776:\"<p>Launching a new website and looking for the best WordPress hosting company for your needs?</p>\n<p>There are 100&#8217;s of WordPress hosting companies out there, and choosing the right one for your site can improve your SEO and boost your sales.</p>\n<p>In this guide, we&#8217;ll discuss how to choose the best WordPress hosting service and the best WordPress hosting companies that we recommend. But before we share our list, let&#8217;s set you up for success and cover the basics of WordPress hosting so you can make an informed decision.</p>\n<h3>What is WordPress Hosting?</h3>\n<p>Web hosting is where your website lives on the internet. So if it helps, think of WordPress hosting as a house where your website&#8217;s files, images, and content are stored.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-495465 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/What-is-the-best-hosting-service-for-WordPress.jpg\" alt=\"What is the best hosting service for WordPress 2019\" width=\"1116\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/What-is-the-best-hosting-service-for-WordPress.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/What-is-the-best-hosting-service-for-WordPress-300x161.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/What-is-the-best-hosting-service-for-WordPress-768x413.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/What-is-the-best-hosting-service-for-WordPress-1024x551.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>On the other hand, <strong>WordPress</strong> hosting is web hosting that&#8217;s designed to be used exclusively with WordPress websites. So, it&#8217;s specially optimized to help your site load quickly. And it often includes other tools and features to make managing your WordPress site easy.</p>\n<h3>Do You Need a Hosting Site for WordPress?</h3>\n<p>If you want to <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">make a website</a> using WordPress.org, then yes, you need a hosting site.</p>\n<p>But if you&#8217;re using WordPress.com, you can obtain a free domain and site without signing up for hosting.</p>\n<p>So still asking yourself is managed WordPress hosting worth it?</p>\n<p>Well, if you want to have control over your website and be able to monetize it, then yes, you do need a hosting site for WordPress. WordPress.org allows you to add <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-free-wordpress-plugins-for-your-website/\">WordPress plugins</a> to add features and customize your website as much as you want.</p>\n<p>WordPress.com isn&#8217;t the right service for most people, so check out our post on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/wordpress-com-vs-wordpress-org-pros-and-cons-compared/\">WordPress.com vs WordPress.org </a>to learn more about why you&#8217;ll probably need a hosting site for WordPress.</p>\n<p>Reading this because you asked which hosting service is best? We&#8217;ll fill you in with all the details next, but first we&#8217;ll show you exactly how to choose the best WordPress hosting (in 2019).</p>\n<h3>How to Choose the Best WordPress Hosting?</h3>\n<p>The best way to choose your website hosting service is to pay attention to these 4 important factors:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Speed</strong>The server load time should be under 300 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>A reliable hosting service will have at least 99% availability</li>\n<li><strong>Customer Service </strong>For help with WordPress related questions</li>\n<li><strong>Your Needs </strong>The hosting service should work with your business size and type</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>How to Figure out Your Hosting Needs?</h3>\n<p>So to figure out which WordPress hosting plan will fit your needs, you&#8217;ll need to know the different kinds. Here are the top 5 web hosting options:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Shared WordPress Hosting.</strong>Themost popular type of WordPress hosting used by beginners offers hosting via a large shared server. Best for small businesses and bloggers.</li>\n<li><strong>Managed WordPress Hosting.</strong>Premium hosting for WordPress specifically that offers bells and whistles that keep you worry free. Best for established sites or bloggers who aren&#8217;t tech savvy and can justify the expense.</li>\n<li><strong>WordPress VPS Hosting. </strong>A Virtual Private Server (<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/best-vps-hosting-compared/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">VPS</a>) can combine the privacy and control of managed hosting while still using a shared server. Best for medium businesses and high-traffic blogs.</li>\n<li><strong>WordPress Dedicated Server Hosting. </strong>A physical server you&#8217;ll lease from the provider for full control.Best for extremely high-traffic sites and blogs employing a system admin.</li>\n<li><strong>Free WordPress Hosting.</strong>There&#8217;s free web hosting out there, but most have some sort of catch like requiring you put their ads on your site. We suggest avoiding free WordPress hosting.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Unless you&#8217;re running an extremely high-traffic site, we recommend our readers start out with<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/the-truth-about-shared-wordpress-web-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">shared WordPress hosting</a>or<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/managed-wordpress-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">managed WordPress hosting</a>.</p>\n<p>So when choosing the best WordPress web hosting, keep in mind that agood WordPress hosting company prioritizes making your site fast so you can improve user experience, rank higher in search engines, and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/research-based-tips-to-improve-contact-form-conversions/\">get more form conversions</a>.</p>\n<p>And a bad WordPress hosting company can lose you visitors because of slow load times and unreliable service.</p>\n<p>So now that you know how to choose the best WordPress host, it&#8217;s time to check out our hand-picked list of the best hosting services for WordPress sites.</p>\n<h3>What Is the Best Hosting Service for WordPress?</h3>\n<p>The companies below specialize in providing the best WordPress hosting and have an excellent support team, which is why we recommend them to WPForms users. They&#8217;ve also agreed to offer our readers exclusive discounts <strong>up to 63% off.</strong></p>\n<p>1. <a title=\"Bluehost\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>Bluehost</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Bluehost\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-495333 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bluehost-wordpress-hosting-best-wordpress-hosting-2019.jpg\" alt=\"bluehost best wordpress hosting 2019\" width=\"1116\" height=\"787\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bluehost-wordpress-hosting-best-wordpress-hosting-2019.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bluehost-wordpress-hosting-best-wordpress-hosting-2019-300x212.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bluehost-wordpress-hosting-best-wordpress-hosting-2019-768x542.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bluehost-wordpress-hosting-best-wordpress-hosting-2019-1024x722.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Bluehost is one of the most popular web hosts on this list, probably because they&#8217;re an official WordPress.org recommended hosting provider. They&#8217;re also consistently rated #1 for small business web hosting, so you can&#8217;t go wrong here.</p>\n<p>And with <a title=\"Bluehost\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Bluehost</a>, you don&#8217;t have to worry about your website being slow just because there&#8217;s a spike in traffic, for instance. In addition, their 24/7 customer service is available by phone, email, or live chat and can help you whenever you need it. They also offer a free domain and free ssl certificates.</p>\n<p>On top of that, prices start at just $2.75 per month.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Speed</strong>: 689 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.99%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 4/5</li>\n<li><strong>Website:</strong>bluehost.com</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a class=\"button\" href=\"http://www.wpforms.com/refer/bluehost\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with Bluehost </a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>2.<a title=\"Siteground\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong> SiteGround</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Siteground\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-495359 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-hosting-comparison.jpg\" alt=\"wordpress hosting comparison siteground best wordpress hosting\" width=\"1116\" height=\"837\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-hosting-comparison.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-hosting-comparison-300x225.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-hosting-comparison-768x576.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-hosting-comparison-1024x768.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Siteground\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/siteground/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SiteGround</a> is another wildly popular WordPress web hosting provider that&#8217;s got sky-high ratings from users. Plus, it&#8217;s also recommend officially by WordPress.org, which is a big deal. And they provide unique in-house WordPress speed and security solutions to make your site as fast and secure as possible.</p>\n<p>Also, SiteGround offers location-specific hosting with 3 different data centers in the USA, Europe, and Asia so you can choose the one closest to you and make sure your site is lightning-fast. Additionally, they offer WordPress daily backups, plus unlimited databases and email accounts.</p>\n<p>And, their prices start at just $3.95 a month.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Speed</strong>: 649 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.98%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 5/5</li>\n<li><strong>Website:</strong>siteground.com</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a class=\"button\" href=\"http://www.wpforms.com/refer/siteground\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with SiteGround </a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>3. <a title=\"Dreamhost\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>DreamHost</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"Dreamhost\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-495412\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/what-is-the-best-wordpress-hosting-2019.jpg\" alt=\"what is the best wordpress hosting 2019\" width=\"1116\" height=\"715\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/what-is-the-best-wordpress-hosting-2019.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/what-is-the-best-wordpress-hosting-2019-300x192.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/what-is-the-best-wordpress-hosting-2019-768x492.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/what-is-the-best-wordpress-hosting-2019-1024x656.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Another officially recommended hosting provider from WordPress.org is DreamHost. This independently owned and operated company is a smart choice because they offer a 97-day money back guarantee. Plus, they&#8217;ve been powering millions of sites since 1997.</p>\n<p>And if you choose DreamHost, you&#8217;ll get acustom dashboard, 1-click WordPress install, automatic updates, unlimited space, unlimited bandwidth, and free SSL certificates. So if youre looking for an excellent WordPress host that offers easy site creation with high-speed SSD storage, then <a title=\"Dreamhost\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">DreamHost</a> could be the right one for you.</p>\n<p>Plus, prices start at just $2.95 a month.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Speed</strong>: 445 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.90%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 4/5</li>\n<li><strong>Website:</strong>dreamhost.com</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a class=\"button\" href=\"http://www.wpforms.com/refer/dreamhost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with DreamHost </a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>4. <a title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>WP Engine</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-495400 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Which-hosting-service-is-best.jpg\" alt=\"wp enngine support team\" width=\"1116\" height=\"780\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Which-hosting-service-is-best.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Which-hosting-service-is-best-300x210.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Which-hosting-service-is-best-768x537.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Which-hosting-service-is-best-1024x716.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></a></p>\n<p>WP Engine is a managed hosting company that&#8217;s used on WordPress specifically. And you know they&#8217;re reliable since they have some popular clients including companies like Yelp, MyFitnessPal, Asana, National Geographic, and PBS. That&#8217;s because they&#8217;re one of the best managed WordPress hosting platforms in the world.</p>\n<p>So if you&#8217;ve got a high-traffic site and need a top-notch host, you&#8217;ll appreciate that <a title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">WP Engine</a> partners withAmazon Web Services and Google Cloud. These partnerships giveyour WordPress website the highest possible availability, speed, scalability, and security. And it all comes with 24/7 customer service.</p>\n<p>In addition, WP Engine plans include the Genesis Framework + multiple <a href=\"http://wpforms.com/refer/studiopress\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">StudioPress</a> themes completely free (an amazing value).</p>\n<p>Prices start at around $20 per month.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Speed</strong>: 582 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.99%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 4/5</li>\n<li><strong>Website:</strong>wpengine.com</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a class=\"button\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with WP Engine </a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>5. <a title=\"HostGator\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>HostGator</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"HostGator\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-495415 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/website-hosting-customer-support.jpg\" alt=\"hostgator best wordpress hosting\" width=\"1116\" height=\"831\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/website-hosting-customer-support.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/website-hosting-customer-support-300x223.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/website-hosting-customer-support-768x572.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/website-hosting-customer-support-1024x762.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"HostGator\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">HostGator</a> supports millions of websites and is a leader in the shared hosting space. They have affordable plans that are backed by a 45-day money back guarantee.</p>\n<p>In addition, all plans include a website builder with templates, unlimited bandwidth, and $100 in AdWords credits to help you optimize your <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress SEO</a>. On top of that, HostGator offers amazing 24/7 support.</p>\n<p>Additionally, prices start at just $2.75 a month.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Speed</strong>: 691 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.96%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 5/5</li>\n<li><strong>Website:</strong>hostgator.com</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a class=\"button\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/hostgator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with HostGator </a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>6. <a title=\"InMotion Hosting\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>InMotion Hosting</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"InMotion Hosting\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-495433 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/inmotion-hosting-offer-wordpress-free-domain.jpg\" alt=\"inmotion hosting customer service\" width=\"1116\" height=\"655\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/inmotion-hosting-offer-wordpress-free-domain.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/inmotion-hosting-offer-wordpress-free-domain-300x176.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/inmotion-hosting-offer-wordpress-free-domain-768x451.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/inmotion-hosting-offer-wordpress-free-domain-1024x601.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></a></p>\n<p>InMotion Hosting&#8217;s many great features include SSD storage, unlimited bandwidth, a free domain, and a 90-day money back guarantee. And unlike most other shared hosting plans, <a title=\"InMotion Hosting\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">InMotion Hosting</a> gives you a choice of data centers so you can pick the one closest to you and improve your page load time.</p>\n<p>Also, we love that they&#8217;re eco-friendly and use advanced Outside Air Cooling tech in their green data center that reduces their carbon output by 2000+ tons per year.</p>\n<p>And prices for InMotion start at only $4.99 per month.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Speed</strong>: 982 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.91%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 4/5</li>\n<li><strong>Website:</strong>inmotionhosting.com</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a class=\"button\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/inmotion-hosting/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with InMotion </a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>7. <a title=\"GreenGeeks\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><strong>GreenGeeks</strong></a></p>\n<p><a title=\"GreenGeeks\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-495446\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/features-include-fastest-wordpress-hosting.jpg\" alt=\"features include fastest wordpress hosting\" width=\"1116\" height=\"657\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/features-include-fastest-wordpress-hosting.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/features-include-fastest-wordpress-hosting-300x177.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/features-include-fastest-wordpress-hosting-768x452.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/features-include-fastest-wordpress-hosting-1024x603.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></a></p>\n<p>The most eco-friendly hosting company on this list is<a title=\"GreenGeeks\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">GreenGeeks</a>. They give back 3x the power they consumeinto the grid in the form of renewable energy, for instance. Also, their SSD storage makes them one of the fastest WordPress hosting providers that also delivers on security and reliability.</p>\n<p>Plus, they&#8217;ve got a 30-day money back guarantee and 24/7 support.</p>\n<p>And their prices start at just $2.95 a month.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Speed</strong>: 697 ms</li>\n<li><strong>Uptime</strong>: 99.92%</li>\n<li><strong>Support</strong>: 4/5</li>\n<li><strong>Website:</strong>greengeeks.com</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a class=\"button\" href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Get started with GreenGeeks </a></p>\n<hr />\n<h3>The Best WordPress Hosting (Winner)</h3>\n<p>So now that you&#8217;ve seen the best WordPress web hosting services and what they have to offer, it&#8217;s time to decide which one is right for you.</p>\n<p>Ideally, you want to pick a service thats fast, in your budget, and promises over 99% uptime. But still asking yourself what is the best WordPress hosting?</p>\n<p>All of the hosting providers on this list are excellent, but our overall recommendation goes to<a title=\"Bluehost\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/greengeeks/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Bluehost</a>.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Bluehost\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/bluehost/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-495765\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bluehost-best-wordpress-hosting-2019.png\" alt=\"bluehost best wordpress hosting 2019\" width=\"558\" height=\"321\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bluehost-best-wordpress-hosting-2019.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/bluehost-best-wordpress-hosting-2019-300x173.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></a></p>\n<p>One of the reasons is because they&#8217;re officially recommended by WordPress.org. Plus, Bluehost is super affordable for blogs and small business websites.</p>\n<p>And if you change your mind down the road, it&#8217;s easy to<a title=\"How to Move One Web Host to Another in 2019 (No Downtime!)\" href=\"https://www.isitwp.com/switch-one-web-host-another-without-downtime-step-by-step/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">switch to a new web host</a>.</p>\n<h3>Speed and Performance Tests</h3>\n<p>We used independent 3rd-party tools like Bitcatcha, Pingdom, and Load Impact to test the performance and reliability of each of these companies, so the data above can help you make a reliable decision.</p>\n<p>So, below are a few speed and performance tests we ran on these web hosting companies:</p>\n<p>1. <strong>Performance</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-494721 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-web-hosting-load-times.jpg\" alt=\"load times\" width=\"558\" height=\"218\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-web-hosting-load-times.jpg 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-web-hosting-load-times-300x117.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>We used Load Impact to analyze the performance of the web hosting server. And we gradually built up to 100 visitors at once because we wanted to see how the servers would handle increased requests from multiple connections at the same time.</p>\n<p>2. <strong>Speed</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-494726 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/installing-wordpress-web-hosting-companies.jpg\" alt=\"installing wordpress\" width=\"558\" height=\"246\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/installing-wordpress-web-hosting-companies.jpg 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/installing-wordpress-web-hosting-companies-300x132.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>We used Pingdom, an industry leading website speed test service, to checkspeed across the hosting companies.</p>\n<p>3. <strong>Server Response Time</strong></p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone wp-image-494732 size-full\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-hosting-plan-load-times.jpg\" alt=\"ssl certificates\" width=\"558\" height=\"162\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-hosting-plan-load-times.jpg 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wordpress-hosting-plan-load-times-300x87.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Bitcatcha helped us determineserver response times across from geographical locations including the US, London, Singapore, Sao Paulo, India, Sydney, and Japan.</p>\n<p>So now you know exactly how we got the scores for the companies on this list.</p>\n<h3>In Conclusion</h3>\n<p>We hope this list of the best WordPress hosting services helped you find the right option for you and your site.</p>\n<p>And if you&#8217;re just installing WordPress and growing your business online, be sure to check out this post on<a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-much-does-a-website-really-cost-beginners-guide/\">how much it really costs to make a website</a>.</p>\n<p>Now that you&#8217;ve got your host, it&#8217;s time to set up your web forms and start collecting leads. Get started with the most powerful<a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WordPress forms plugin</a>today.</p>\n<p>And if you like this article, then please follow us on<a href=\"http://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Facebook</a>and<a href=\"https://twitter.com/easywpforms?lang=en\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Twitter</a>for more from the WPForms blog.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/best-wordpress-hosting-guide/\">How to Choose the Best WordPress Hosting (Ultimate Guide for 2019)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.c