}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"conversions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=492168\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:575:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited to share with you that WPForms 1.5.3 has just been released and it&#8217;s got some great new features. This update makes it even easier to use the most beginner-friendly form plugin in the market. Plus, your forms are getting smarter and faster so you can get even more conversions on your site. With [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/announcing-wpforms-1-5-3/\">Announcing WPForms 1.5.3  AJAX, Google reCAPTCHA v3 + AMP Support</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Lisa Gennaro\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9402:\"<p>We&#8217;re excited to share with you that WPForms 1.5.3 has just been released and it&#8217;s got some great new features.</p>\n<p>This update makes it even easier to use the most beginner-friendly form plugin in the market. Plus, your forms are getting smarter and faster so you can get even more conversions on your site.</p>\n<p>With that, lets take a look at whats new in WPForms 1.5.3.</p>\n<h3>Created AJAX Form Submissions</h3>\n<p>With our latest update, you can now prevent a page from refreshing when someone submit a form.</p>\n<p>WPForms now lets you enable AJAX form submissions in the form settings.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-492188\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/ajax-form-submissions.jpg\" alt=\"ajax form submissions\" width=\"558\" height=\"291\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/ajax-form-submissions.jpg 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/ajax-form-submissions-300x156.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /><br />\nThis is especially useful in <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/exit-intent-popup-examples/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">popups</a>, overlays, modal windows, and with file upload fields. Without AJAX form submission enabled, the entire page would need to refresh after someone hits submit. This could cause a popup or modal window to close, and users could miss important confirmation messages that keeps them engaged.</p>\n<p>Now, with AJAX mode enabled, there&#8217;s no need for the page to reload after someone hits submit.</p>\n<p>The user stays on the same page, sees a spinning wheel confirming the form is processing, and receives a confirmation message  an improved user experience so you get even more leads, faster.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-492197\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/ajaxformsubmissions.gif\" alt=\"ajaxformsubmissions\" width=\"558\" height=\"376\" /></p>\n<p>Learn more about <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-enable-ajax-form-submissions/\">how to enable AJAX form submissions here</a>.</p>\n<p>We think you and your website visitors will find it&#8217;s a better, faster experience overall.</p>\n<h3>Added Google reCAPTCHA v3 Option</h3>\n<p>We&#8217;ve had a lot of you request it, so now Google reCAPTCHA v3 setup for WPForms is here. It can be found under Settings reCAPTCHA.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-491270\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Open-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms.jpg\" alt=\"Open reCAPTCHA settings in WPForms\" width=\"1116\" height=\"798\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Open-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Open-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms-300x215.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Open-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms-768x549.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Open-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms-1024x732.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>Google&#8217;s reCAPTCHA v3 was released in fall of 2018 and runs completely in the background of your site. Your visitors don&#8217;t see a checkbox (like v2 Checkbox reCAPTCHA) and aren&#8217;t asked to answer any image-based questions (like v2 Invisible reCAPTCHA) to ensure they&#8217;re human.</p>\n<p>Similar to v2, when someone loads a page, v3 tries to check and do some logic to see if it thinks it&#8217;s a spammer or a bot.</p>\n<p>But the main difference with reCAPTCHA v3 is that there&#8217;s no test for the user to complete to prove they&#8217;re human.</p>\n<p>On the back-end, v3 automatically gives a score for the user. If that score falls below your Score Threshold (found in settings) theuser can&#8217;t submit the form at all. Which could be a plus or minus, depending on how you want your forms set up.</p>\n<p>Not only does our new release give you the chance to choose to use Google reCAPTCHA v3 and adjust your Score Threshold, but you can now also edit the Fail Message.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-492235\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Additional-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms-edit-fail-message.jpg\" alt=\"Additional-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms-edit-fail-message\" width=\"1116\" height=\"749\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Additional-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms-edit-fail-message.jpg 1116w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Additional-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms-edit-fail-message-300x201.jpg 300w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Additional-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms-edit-fail-message-768x515.jpg 768w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/Additional-reCAPTCHA-settings-in-WPForms-edit-fail-message-1024x687.jpg 1024w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1116px) 100vw, 1116px\" /></p>\n<p>This is extra helpful if you want to add the score Google recorded for the failed attempt to your fail message so visitors can see it. That when, your users can tell you what their score was if you&#8217;re troubleshooting and find you need to lower your Score Threshold.</p>\n<p>To learn exactly how to setup reCAPTCHA and for more on which version may be right for your site, check out <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-custom-captcha-addon-in-wpforms/\">how to install and use theCustom Captcha addon in WPForms</a>.</p>\n<p>With the newest WPForms update, it&#8217;s now easier than ever to add any version of reCAPTCHA to your forms.</p>\n<h3>Added Google AMP Compatibility</h3>\n<p>WPForms Lite now includes full compatibility for Google AMP.</p>\n<p>Google AMP, or Accelerated Mobile Project, is an open source initiative with the goal of making web content load faster on mobile. If you&#8217;ve done a Google search on your mobile devices, odds are you&#8217;ve visited an AMP-enhanced web page. It&#8217;s quickly becoming the standard viewing experience for publishers.</p>\n<p>For a page to be 100% AMP compatible, it enforces various strict requirements on what can run on the back end of your site. That&#8217;s why the entire experience is near instant. Notably, it doesn&#8217;t allow loading extra javascript to enhance functionality.</p>\n<p>But in WPForms Lite version 1.5.3, all your forms will work perfectly with the AMP plugin, and pass those strict validation requirements. Plus, you&#8217;ll get more submits since the user experience is so fast.</p>\n<p>While Google AMP compatibility is currently only available for WPForms Lite, we&#8217;re looking forward to bringing improved compatibility to Pro users in the near future. It&#8217;s also important to note that Google reCAPTCHA v2 isn&#8217;t supported, so you&#8217;ll need to use the new reCAPTCHA v3 if you want enhanced spam protection with AMP.</p>\n<p>For a more in-depth tutorial, check out our guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-use-wpforms-with-amp/\">how to use WPForms with AMP</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-492244\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/AMP-and-wpforms.jpg\" alt=\"AMP and wpforms\" width=\"558\" height=\"275\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/AMP-and-wpforms.jpg 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/AMP-and-wpforms-300x148.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>We worked in partnership with the Google team to bring these exciting new AMP capabilities to WPForms.</p>\n<p>We also want to thank <a title=\"WPEngine\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/wpengine/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">WP Engine</a> and the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/refer/studiopress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">StudioPress</a> team for helping us throughout to make sure that WPForms AMP and other features work seamlessly with the new Genesis AMP update.</p>\n<h3>Added French + Portuguese (Brazilian) Translations</h3>\n<p>We know that if you&#8217;re using WordPress is a language besides English and your site&#8217;s plugins aren&#8217;t translated too, if can create inconsistencies and make building a website harder than it should be.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s why we&#8217;ve added even more translations to the world&#8217;s favorite contact form plugin.</p>\n<p>WPForms 1.5.3 brings the new capability to fully translate into:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>French</li>\n<li>Portuguese (Brazilian)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>We want to make it easy for anyone to use WPForms, even if English isn&#8217;t your native language. We&#8217;ve got a handy guide on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-translate-wpforms-into-a-different-language/\">how to translate WPForms into a different language</a> for you to check out, too.</p>\n<p>And that covers the WPForms 1.5.3 update and its cool new features.</p>\n<p>Give it a spin and let us know any thoughts you have, we&#8217;re always here for our users.</p>\n<p>Ready to experience the speed and ease of WPForms Pro? <a href=\"http://wpforms.com/pricing\">Click here to get started today</a>.</p>\n<p>As always, thank you for your continued support of WPForms. We look forward to bringing you more updates soon!</p>\n<p><em>Lisa and the WPForms team</em></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/announcing-wpforms-1-5-3/\">Announcing WPForms 1.5.3  AJAX, Google reCAPTCHA v3 + AMP Support</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"https://wpforms.com/announcing-wpforms-1-5-3/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"2\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:50:\"How to Create a Custom Airtable Form for WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-custom-airtable-form-for-wordpress/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-custom-airtable-form-for-wordpress/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 17 Jun 2019 12:00:15 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:19:\"WordPress Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:14:\"wordpress form\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"zapier\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"WPForms\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"zapier addon\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:29:\"https://wpforms.com/?p=489916\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:572:\"<p>Do you want to create a custom Airtable form for your WordPress site? Airtable is a cloud service that combines the power of spreadsheets and databases together. It allows you to build custom spreadsheet apps without writing a single line of code. In this article, we&#8217;ll show you the step by step process on how [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-custom-airtable-form-for-wordpress/\">How to Create a Custom Airtable Form for WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:18:\"Sandipan Mukherjee\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26311:\"<p>Do you want to create a custom Airtable form for your WordPress site? Airtable is a cloud service that combines the power of spreadsheets and databases together. It allows you to build custom spreadsheet apps without writing a single line of code.</p>\n<p>In this article, we&#8217;ll show you the step by step process on how to create a custom Airtable form and embed it to your WordPress site.</p>\n<h3>Why Create a Custom Airtable Form in WordPress?</h3>\n<p>Airtable helps you to build custom spreadsheet apps to store information, just like you would do in a database.</p>\n<p>It creates easy to use and visually appealing spreadsheets that can be used for product planning, user studies, sales CRM (<a href=\"https://wpforms.com/top-crms-for-your-small-business/\">Customer Relationship Management</a>), product launches, content calendar planning, and more.</p>\n<p>However, you&#8217;ll have to enter all the data in your Airtable account manually.</p>\n<p>To avoid this problem, you can <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/guides/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">start a WordPress site</a> and then create a custom Airtable form with the help of the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WPForms</a> plugin.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490555\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-plugin-for-wordpress.png\" alt=\"WPForms plugin for WordPress\" width=\"558\" height=\"254\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-plugin-for-wordpress.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-plugin-for-wordpress-300x137.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>WPForms is the best form builder plugin and comes with <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-the-form-templates-pack-addon/\">different types of form templates</a>. So you can easily build any kind of formbased on your requirements.</p>\n<p>Finally, you can connect the form to your <a href=\"https://airtable.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Airtable</a> account using Zapier. So whenever someone submits the form, the data will be added to your Airtable account automatically. Cool, isn&#8217;t it?</p>\n<p>This will help you save your valuable time and increase your productivity.</p>\n<p>So without further ado, let&#8217;s get started with the process of creating a custom Airtable form for your WordPress site.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Create a WordPress Form</h3>\n<p>We&#8217;ll be creating a simple contact form for the sake of this tutorial. Then, we&#8217;ll show you how to connect this form to your Airtable account.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll assume that you want to create this form to add the entries automatically to the <strong>Contacts</strong> table of your &#8220;Sales CRM&#8221; workspace.</p>\n<p>So the first thing you need to do is install and activate the <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/pricing/\">WPForms</a> plugin. You may check out the beginner&#8217;s guide on <a href=\"http://www.wpbeginner.com/beginners-guide/step-by-step-guide-to-install-a-wordpress-plugin-for-beginners/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">how to install a WordPress plugin</a> in case you need any help.</p>\n<p>Upon activation, you need to go to <strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>Add New</strong> to create a new form.</p>\n<p>On the Setup page, you&#8217;ll have to change the <strong>Form Name</strong> to any name of your choice. Next, you need to click on the Simple Contact Form template to create the custom Airtable form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-491932\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-custom-airtable-form.png\" alt=\"Create Custom Airtable form\" width=\"558\" height=\"306\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-custom-airtable-form.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-custom-airtable-form-300x165.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll be adding some basic fields like name, email, organization name, and phone number to this form. You can follow our tutorial on <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-create-a-simple-contact-form-in-wordpress/\">how to create a simple contact form</a> for detailed instructions.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-491937\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/custom-airtable-form-demo.png\" alt=\"Custom Airtable Form Demo\" width=\"558\" height=\"403\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/custom-airtable-form-demo.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/custom-airtable-form-demo-300x217.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;re done with the customization part, you can <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/setup-form-notification-wpforms/\">make changes to the notification</a> and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/setup-form-confirmation-wpforms/\">confirmation settings</a> of this form.</p>\n<p>Finally, you need to click on the <strong>Save</strong> button, present at the top-right corner of your screen, to store the changes.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-491940\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/save-custom-airtable-form.png\" alt=\"Save Custom Airtable form\" width=\"558\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/save-custom-airtable-form.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/save-custom-airtable-form-300x140.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<h3>Step 2: Embed the Form to Your Website</h3>\n<p>In this step, we&#8217;ll embed the custom Airtable form to our website and then, we&#8217;ll add at least one test entry to the form.</p>\n<p>But why do we need to add a test entry? The reason is we&#8217;ll be using it later to test the connection between WPForms and Airtable. This will assure us that everything is working properly.</p>\n<p>You can easily embed the form to a post, page, or <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-add-a-contact-form-in-wordpress-sidebar-widget/\">the sidebar of your website</a>. Let&#8217;s take a look at how to embed it to a WordPress page.</p>\n<p>First, you need to head over to <strong>Pages</strong>  <strong>Add New</strong> from the left sidebar of your WordPress admin panel.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490551\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/adding-wpforms-block-to-a-wordpress-page.png\" alt=\"Adding WPForms block to a WordPress page\" width=\"558\" height=\"319\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/adding-wpforms-block-to-a-wordpress-page.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/adding-wpforms-block-to-a-wordpress-page-300x172.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you should click on the Add block (<strong>+</strong>) icon to insert the WPForms block.</p>\n<p>This will open the block manager where you need to search for the WPForms block and then click on it to add it to the page editor.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490552\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-from-wpforms-dropdown-box.png\" alt=\"Select custom Airtable form from WPForms dropdown box\" width=\"558\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-from-wpforms-dropdown-box.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-from-wpforms-dropdown-box-300x128.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once the WPForms block is added, you need to select the custom Airtable form from the dropdown menu. This will add the form to the page editor.</p>\n<p>Finally, you need to publish this page by clicking on the <strong>Publish</strong> button, present at the top-right corner of the screen.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-491942\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/publish-page-with-custom-airtable-form.png\" alt=\"Publish page with custom Airtable form\" width=\"558\" height=\"293\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/publish-page-with-custom-airtable-form.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/publish-page-with-custom-airtable-form-300x158.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Now go ahead and open this page in a new tab of your web browser. And then, fill in the form and click on the <strong>Submit</strong> button to create a test form entry.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Install Zapier Addon</h3>\n<p>The next thing you need to do is <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/how-to-install-and-use-zapier-addon-with-wpforms/\">install the Zapier addon</a>.</p>\n<p>In case you don&#8217;t know, Zapier is an automation tool that lets you connect 2 or more apps to do a particular task. Hence, we&#8217;ll be using Zapier to connect WPForms and Airtable.</p>\n<p>To install the Zapier addon, you need to go to the <strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>Addons</strong> page and then search for that addon. Once you find it, you should <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/docs/install-activate-wpforms-addons/\">install and activate the Zapier addon</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490404\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-and-activate-zapier-addon.png\" alt=\"Install and Activate Zapier addon\" width=\"558\" height=\"225\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-and-activate-zapier-addon.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/install-and-activate-zapier-addon-300x121.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Now head over to <strong>WPForms</strong>  <strong>Settings</strong> page to get the Zapier API key. This key will be used to connect Zapier to WPForms account.</p>\n<p>On the WPForms settings page, you need to click on the <strong>Integrations</strong> tab. And then, you should click on the Zapier logo to find the API key for your site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490403\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/get-zapier-api-key-to-connect-wpforms-account.png\" alt=\"Get Zapier API key to connect WPForms account\" width=\"558\" height=\"373\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/get-zapier-api-key-to-connect-wpforms-account.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/get-zapier-api-key-to-connect-wpforms-account-300x201.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>You must keep this page open as we&#8217;ll use this API key later in <strong>Step 5</strong>.</p>\n<h3>Step 4: Create a New Zap</h3>\n<p>To connect WPForms and Airtable, you need to create a new Zap on the Zapier website.</p>\n<p>Wait! What is a Zap? It is a process of connecting 2 or more apps and it always needs a trigger to perform a specific action.</p>\n<p>In a new tab of your web browser, you should open the <a href=\"https://zapier.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Zapier</a> website and log in to your account. You can create a new account for free if you don&#8217;t have one.</p>\n<p>On the Zapier dashboard, you need to click on the <strong>Make a Zap!</strong> button, present at the top-right corner of your screen, to start the configuration wizard.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490412\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/make-a-zap-button.png\" alt=\"Make a Zap button\" width=\"558\" height=\"228\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/make-a-zap-button.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/make-a-zap-button-300x123.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, the process of creating a zap comprises of two parts.In the first part, you&#8217;ll have to set up WPForms as the trigger app. And then, you&#8217;ll need to configure Airtable as the action app.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s get started with the trigger setup process.</p>\n<h3>Step 5: Configure the Trigger App</h3>\n<p>To configure WPForms as the trigger app, the first thing you need to do is search for WPForms app using the &#8220;Choose a Trigger App&#8221; search box.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490420\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/choose-wpforms-as-a-trigger-app.png\" alt=\"Choose WPForms as a trigger app\" width=\"558\" height=\"167\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/choose-wpforms-as-a-trigger-app.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/choose-wpforms-as-a-trigger-app-300x90.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you find it, you should click on it to proceed.</p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll have to select &#8220;New Form Entry&#8221; as the trigger option and then click on the <strong>Save + Continue</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490421\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-new-form-entry-as-wpforms-trigger-option.png\" alt=\"Select New Form Entry as WPForms trigger option\" width=\"558\" height=\"228\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-new-form-entry-as-wpforms-trigger-option.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-new-form-entry-as-wpforms-trigger-option-300x123.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s time to connect the WPForms account to Zapier now. You can skip this part if you&#8217;ve previously connected your WPForms account to Zapier.</p>\n<p>On the other hand, you should click on the <strong>Connect an Account</strong> button if you&#8217;re doing this for the first time.</p>\n<p>This will open a popup window where you will be asked to enter your website URL and the Zapier API key.You may go back to <strong>Step 3</strong> to understand how to get the API key.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490419\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-wpforms-account.png\" alt=\"Allow Zapier to access WPForms account\" width=\"558\" height=\"393\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-wpforms-account.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-wpforms-account-300x211.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once you&#8217;ve filled in the details, you need to click on the <strong>Yes, Continue</strong> button.</p>\n<p>This will close the popup window and now you&#8217;ll see your WPForms account added to the &#8220;Select WPForms Account&#8221; page.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490434\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-connection-between-zapier-and-wpforms.png\" alt=\"Test Connection between Zapier and WPForms\" width=\"558\" height=\"274\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-connection-between-zapier-and-wpforms.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-connection-between-zapier-and-wpforms-300x147.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>You can click on the <strong>Test</strong> button to check the connection between WPForms and Zapier. If you receive a success message, then you should click on the <strong>Save + Continue</strong> button to proceed.</p>\n<p>Zapier will now access your WPForms account and fetch all the formsof your website. So go ahead and select the custom Airtable form from the dropdown box on the &#8220;Set up WPForms Form Entry&#8221; page.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-491946\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-custom-airtable-form-from-dropdown-menu.png\" alt=\"Select Custom Airtable Form from dropdown menu\" width=\"558\" height=\"269\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-custom-airtable-form-from-dropdown-menu.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-custom-airtable-form-from-dropdown-menu-300x145.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once done, you need to click on the <strong>Continue</strong> button to proceed.</p>\n<p>Next, all the entries of your form will be retrieved by Zapier. You need to select any one of the form entries so that it can be used for testing the connection between WPForms and Airtable later.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490437\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-entry-for-testing-purpose.png\" alt=\"Select Custom Airtable Form Entry for testing purpose\" width=\"558\" height=\"328\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-entry-for-testing-purpose.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-form-entry-for-testing-purpose-300x176.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Finally, you should click on the <strong>Continue</strong> button to complete the trigger setup process.</p>\n<h3>Step 6: Configure an Action App</h3>\n<p>Let&#8217;s start the configuration process of the action app.To do that, you should click on the &#8220;Your Zap currently lacks an Action step. Add one now!&#8221; link.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490466\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/zap-lacks-an-action-app.png\" alt=\"Zap lacks an action app\" width=\"558\" height=\"136\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/zap-lacks-an-action-app.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/zap-lacks-an-action-app-300x73.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Next, you&#8217;ll have to search for the Airtable app using the &#8220;Choose an Action App&#8221; search box and then click on it to proceed.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490470\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/choose-airtable-as-an-action-app.png\" alt=\"Choose Airtable as an Action App\" width=\"558\" height=\"151\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/choose-airtable-as-an-action-app.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/choose-airtable-as-an-action-app-300x81.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Zapier will now ask you to select which Airtable action you want to happen when someone submits the custom Airtable form.</p>\n<p>Since you want to add a new contact to the <strong>Contacts</strong> table of your &#8220;Sales CRM&#8221; workspace, select the <strong>Create Record</strong> option and then click on the <strong>Save + Continue</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490471\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-an-airtable-action-option.png\" alt=\"Select an Airtable action option\" width=\"558\" height=\"288\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-an-airtable-action-option.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/select-an-airtable-action-option-300x155.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>It&#8217;s time to connect your Airtable account to Zapier.</p>\n<p>To do that, you&#8217;ll have to click on the <strong>Connect an Account</strong> button. This will open a pop window asking you to enter the Airtable API key.</p>\n<p>So keep this popup window open and visit the <a href=\"https://airtable.com/account\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Airtable account page</a> in a new tab. Here you need to find the API section which has a textbox with some hidden text.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490477\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/airtable-api-key-to-connect-to-zapier.png\" alt=\"Airtable API key to connect to Zapier\" width=\"558\" height=\"158\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/airtable-api-key-to-connect-to-zapier.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/airtable-api-key-to-connect-to-zapier-300x85.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll have to click on that textbox to view the Airtable API key. Now copy the API key and paste it to the textbox in the Zapier popup window.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490478\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-airtable-account.png\" alt=\"Allow Zapier to access Airtable account\" width=\"558\" height=\"256\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-airtable-account.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/allow-zapier-to-access-airtable-account-300x138.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Once done, you need to click on the <strong>Yes, Continue</strong> button to connect Airtable to Zapier.</p>\n<p>This will close the popup window and you&#8217;ll now see your Airtable account added to the &#8220;Select Airtable Account&#8221; page.</p>\n<p>You may check the connection between Zapier and Airtable by clicking on the <strong>Test</strong> button.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490479\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-connection-between-zapier-and-airtable.png\" alt=\"Test connection between Zapier and Airtable\" width=\"558\" height=\"274\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-connection-between-zapier-and-airtable.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/test-connection-between-zapier-and-airtable-300x147.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>If you get a success message, then you need to click on the <strong>Save + Continue</strong> button to proceed to the next step.</p>\n<h3>Step 7: Setup and Test the Airtable Template</h3>\n<p>Zapier will now ask you to set up the template that will be used to create a new contact in your Airtable account.</p>\n<p>Let&#8217;s take a look at how to configure this template.</p>\n<p>First, you&#8217;ll have to select a <strong>Base</strong>in which you want to add the contact details. This will be fetched from your Airtable account.</p>\n<p>Since we want to add the new contacts to the Sales CRM, you should select <strong>Sales CRM</strong>from the dropdown menu.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-491947\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-template-for-airtable.png\" alt=\"Create template for Airtable\" width=\"558\" height=\"256\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-template-for-airtable.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-template-for-airtable-300x138.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Similarly, you need to select the <strong>Contacts</strong> table from the <strong>Table</strong> dropdown box. This will add a number of new fields to this template.</p>\n<p>You should note that all the new fields are optional, so it depends on you which one you want to edit. Also, Zapier will fetch the data from your Custom Airtable form for these additional fields.</p>\n<p>For the <strong>Name and Org</strong> field, you need to click on the Insert a Field icon and then select <strong>Name</strong> from the dropdown menu. And then, you should select <strong>Organization</strong> from the <strong>Account</strong> dropdown box.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-491983\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-template-to-fetch-data-from-custom-airtable-form.png\" alt=\"Create template to fetch data from Custom Airtable form\" width=\"558\" height=\"339\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-template-to-fetch-data-from-custom-airtable-form.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/create-template-to-fetch-data-from-custom-airtable-form-300x182.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>Similarly, you can edit the email, phone, and name fields in this template.Once you&#8217;re done, you need to scroll down to the bottom of the page and then click on the <strong>Continue</strong> button.</p>\n<p>Next, you can click on the <strong>Send Test to Airtable</strong> button to check the connection between WPForms and Airtable.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-491955\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/send-test-to-airtable.png\" alt=\"Send test to Airtable\" width=\"558\" height=\"157\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/send-test-to-airtable.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/send-test-to-airtable-300x84.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>This will create a new contact with the test form entry in your Airtable account. You can confirm the same by going to your <a href=\"https://airtable.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Airtable</a> account.</p>\n<p>If the new contact is created successfully, then you should return to the Zapier configuration wizard and click on the <strong>Finish</strong> button to complete the action setup process.</p>\n<p>Finally, you need to click on the toggle box to turn it to <strong>ON</strong>. This will ensure that new contacts will be added to your Airtable account whenever someone submits the custom form.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-490379\" src=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-to-airtable-zap.png\" alt=\"WPForms to Airtable zap\" width=\"558\" height=\"324\" srcset=\"https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-to-airtable-zap.png 558w, https://wpforms.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/06/wpforms-to-airtable-zap-300x174.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 558px) 100vw, 558px\" /></p>\n<p>You may also give a name of your choice to this Zap for future reference.</p>\n<p>Congratulations! You have successfully created a custom Airtable form for your WordPress site. You can follow this step by step tutorial to create different types of custom Airtable forms.</p>\n<p>If you liked this article, then you may also check out our guide on<a href=\"https://wpforms.com/how-to-get-an-sms-text-message-from-your-wordpress-form/\">how to get an SMS text message from your WordPress form</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, please follow us on <a href=\"https://facebook.com/wpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a>and<a href=\"https://twitter.com/easywpforms\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a>to get updates from our blog.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-custom-airtable-form-for-wordpress/\">How to Create a Custom Airtable Form for WordPress</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://wpforms.com\">WPForms</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"https://wpforms.com/create-a-custom-airtable-form-for-wordpress/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\